The smoking area must have air extraction systems that allow constant air renewal, so that concentrations of smoke are not generated in the work environment. 3. The smoking area must be properly identified by means of visible and clear signs, so that anyone can easily identify it. 4. The smoking area must be physically separated and incommunicado from spaces that are 100% free of tobacco smoke and emissions, and must not be an obligatory passage for people or be located at the entrances or exits of the buildings. 5. In the measurement of the total space, the surface destined to the provision of the service will be taken into account exclusively, without including in any case the areas destined to the kitchen, to the preparation of drinks, to the sound equipment and its operators, to the toilets or parking lots. 6. The smoking area must be located in a perimeter fence of at least ten meters from the entrances, accesses, exits or any obligatory place where people pass or congregate, as well as from the places where there are air inlet ducts. 7. The smoking area should not occupy more than 10% of the total area of the property or establishment. 8. In the smoking area, it is prohibited to provide any service or consume food, drinks or entertainment, among others, as well as carry out social or recreational activities. 9. The smoking area must have signs that prohibit the entry of minors, which must be visible and adequate. 10. The smoking area is prohibited for pregnant women, the elderly and anyone with a condition that could be aggravated by tobacco smoke.** - Variations by <@770099524416569344> (fast)
